Title: Pokegama Lake Dam
Riddle:
In the land where the north winds blow, 
A guardian of waters, standing low. 
Born from ambition, with control in its grasp, 
Holding back the lake, in its concrete clasp. 

A tale of progress, nature's bound friend, 
In Grand Rapids' embrace, where the waters bend. 
Its name a secret, for you to unveil, 
A monument to engineering, in this watery tale.  

What am I, a keeper of lake and stream, 
A silent watcher in the sunbeam? 
Uncover my name, with history entwined, 
In Grand Rapids’ heart, what will you find?
